Task 1: CSS Basics
Definition: CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style HTML elements, providing control over layout, colors, fonts, and overall presentation.
Role in Web Development: CSS separates content (HTML) from presentation (CSS), allowing for cleaner, more maintainable code and enabling flexible design.

HTML:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <title>CSS Basics</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My Webpage</h1>
    <p>This page has styled background, text color, and font size.</p>
</body>
</html>

CSS:

body {
    background-color: #f0f8ff; /* Light blue background */
    color: #333333;           /* Dark gray text */
    font-size: 18px;          /* Font size for body text */
}
 

 
